{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e4e8599d-e042-493e-8a6e-b2a972d5584f","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws<T>` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName);\n}\n```\n\n**Why modernize:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs (e.g., the constructor could throw instead of `CreateUser`).\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call and lets you inspect the exception (message, properties, inner exception).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"67df3a6e-f891-4655-a73b-d17e79480a88","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question - no tools needed.","outputTokens":246,"requestId":"3419:1CD05C:CCE23B:EE49CA:69F40273"},"id":"67963922-67b7-49d1-b862-0344b8d266ab","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:31:38.470Z","parentId":"c1a8c837-af6a-4d76-aa92-fe3f1d78cd88"}
